‘One on one you have to be able to put your head down and get stuck in. He constantly holds really good width and the players inside him can get the ball to him. He’s a brilliant finisher, but he’s got that power as well.’

As a finisher, Savea is on course to trump his idol and be the greatest there has ever been. No matter how well they prepare, England will struggle to contain him.

